50|$|Cisco HDLC (also {{known as}} cHDLC) is an {{extension}} to the High-Level <b>Data</b> <b>Link</b> Control network <b>protocol</b> created by Cisco Systems, Inc. HDLC is a bit-oriented synchronous <b>data</b> <b>link</b> layer <b>protocol</b> that was originally developed by the International Organization for Standardization (ISO). Often described as being a proprietary extension, the workings of cHDLC have in fact been openly and widely distributed, and the protocol has been implemented by many different network equipment vendors.|$|R
